.TH GOLDENRNG 1 "February 2026" "Golden RNG Enterprise v5.0"
.SH NAME
goldenrng \- Cryptographic Random Number Generator (CSPRNG)

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B goldenrng
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.PP
.B goldenrng
\fB\-m\fR \fIMODE\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\fBGolden RNG Enterprise\fR is a high-performance cryptographic random number 
generator (CSPRNG) implementing the \fBAUR3ES\fR (Animated Universal Randomized 
Diffusion with Enhanced Security) algorithm with SHA-512 key derivation.
.PP
This software is suitable for:
.IP \(bu 2
Cryptographic key generation
.IP \(bu
Secure token generation
.IP \(bu
Monte Carlo simulations
.IP \(bu
Statistical sampling
.IP \(bu
Gaming and lottery applications
.IP \(bu
Security token generation

.SH OPTIONS

.SS "Operation Modes"
.TP
\fB\-m, \-\-mode\fR \fIMODE\fR
Select operation mode. Available modes:
.RS
.TP
\fBstdout\fR
Generate random bytes to stdout (default)
.TP
\fBfile\fR
Write random data to specified file
.TP
\fBstats\fR
Display RNG internal statistics and health status
.TP
\fBtest\fR
Run basic random number quality tests
.TP
\fBsimulate\fR
Monte Carlo Pi estimation simulation
.TP
\fBbenchmark\fR
Run parallel throughput benchmark
.TP
\fBsimd\fR
SIMD benchmark with CPU feature detection
.TP
\fBkat\fR
Known Answer Tests for algorithm verification
.TP
\fBunittests\fR
Complete unit test suite
.TP
\fBdeterminism\fR
Verify deterministic behavior with same seed
.TP
\fBadvanced\fR
Full statistical test battery (NIST SP 800-22 style)
.RE

.SS "Output Options"
.TP
\fB\-o, \-\-output\fR \fIFILE\fR
Write output to \fIFILE\fR instead of stdout
.TP
\fB\-d, \-\-dist\fR \fIDIST\fR
Output distribution type:
.RS
.TP
\fBbytes\fR
Raw random bytes (default)
.TP
\fBuniform\fR
Uniformly distributed integers
.TP
\fBnormal\fR
Gaussian normally distributed numbers
.RE

.TP
\fB\-s, \-\-size\fR \fISIZE\fR
Amount of data to generate. Suffixes:
.RS
.TP
\fBK\fR
Kilobytes (1024)
.TP
\fBM\fR
Megabytes (1024*1024)
.TP
\fBG\fR
Gigabytes (1024*1024*1024)
.RE

.SS "Configuration Options"
.TP
\fB\-\-seed\fR \fISEED\fR
Use \fISEED\fR for deterministic mode (hex or string)
.TP
\fB\-t, \-\-threads\fR \fINUM\fR
Number of threads for parallel benchmarks (default: CPU count)
.TP
\fB\-\-config\fR \fIFILE\fR
Read configuration from \fIFILE\fR

.SS "General Options"
.TP
\fB\-v, \-\-verbose\fR
Enable verbose output with detailed progress
.TP
\fB\-V, \-\-version\fR
Show version information and exit
.TP
\fB\-\-version-full\fR
Show detailed version info (compiler, build date, git commit)
.TP
\fB\-h, \-\-help\fR
Display this help message and exit
.TP
\fB\-\-help\fR
Display extended help with examples

.SH EXAMPLES

.PP
\fBBasic usage - generate random data to stdout:\fR
.RS
.B goldenrng
.RE

.PP
\fBGenerate 10 megabytes to a file:\fR
.RS
.B goldenrng \-m file \-o random.bin \-s 10M
.RE

.PP
\fBGenerate 1 gigabyte with 4 threads:\fR
.RS
.B goldenrng \-m file \-o large.bin \-s 1G \-t 4
.RE

.PP
\fBRun full test suite:\fR
.RS
.B goldenrng \-m advanced
.RE

.PP
\fBRun parallel benchmark with 100MB:\fR
.RS
.B goldenrng \-m benchmark \-s 100M \-t 4
.RE

.PP
\fBTest SIMD optimizations:\fR
.RS
.B goldenrng \-m simd \-s 50M
.RE

.PP
\fBGenerate deterministic output with seed:\fR
.RS
.B goldenrng \-\-seed "MySecretSeed" \-s 1K
.RE

.PP
\fBShow RNG statistics:\fR
.RS
.B goldenrng \-m stats
.RE

.SH ALGORITHM

.PP
The \fBAUR3ES\fR algorithm is a cryptographically secure PRNG combining:
.IP \(bu 2
512-bit internal state (8 × 64-bit words)
.IP \(bu
SHA-512 based key derivation
.IP \(bu
4 rounds of non-linear mixing per block
.IP \(bu
Counter mode output transformation
.IP \(bu
Automatic reseeding from system entropy
.IP \(bu
Golden constant mixing for diffusion enhancement

.SS "Entropy Sources"
.PP
The generator collects entropy from multiple sources:
.IP \(bu 2
Linux \fBgetrandom()\fR syscall
.IP \(bu
\fB/dev/urandom\fR
.IP \(bu
Intel RDRAND/RDSEED (when available)
.IP \(bu
CPU timing jitter
.IP \(bu
High-resolution timers

.SH PERFORMANCE

.PP
Typical performance on modern hardware (8-core CPU @ 3.5GHz):
.IP \(bu 2
\fBSequential:\fR ~257-280 MB/s
.IP \(bu
\fBParallel (4 threads):\fR ~893 MB/s (3.32x speedup)
.IP \(bu
\fBParallel (8 threads):\fR ~1200+ MB/s
.IP \(bu
\fBSIMD optimized:\fR AVX2/AVX-512 acceleration when available

