.SH SECURITY FEATURES

.PP
.IP \(bu 2
\fBSecure memory zeroing\fR - All sensitive data zeroed after use
.IP \(bu
\fBMemory locking\fR - mlock() to prevent swapping to disk
.IP \(bu
\fBConstant-time operations\fR - Timing-safe comparisons
.IP \(bu
\fBEntropy validation\fR - Health checks on entropy sources
.IP \(bu
\fBThread-safe\fR - Full concurrent access support
.IP \(bu
\fBInput validation\fR - All public APIs validate parameters
.IP \(bu
\fBError handling\fR - Graceful degradation on entropy failure

.SH CONFIGURATION

.PP
Configuration is read from the following locations (in order):
.IP \(bu 2
Command line arguments
.IP \(bu
\fI/etc/goldenrng/goldenrng.conf\fR
.IP \(bu
\fI~/.config/goldenrng.conf\fR
.IP \(bu
Built-in defaults

.SS "Configuration File Format"
.PP
Example \fB/etc/goldenrng/goldenrng.conf\fR:
.RS
.nf
# Golden RNG Configuration

# Output mode (stdout, file, stats, test, etc.)
mode=stdout

# Default size suffix (K, M, G)
default_size=1M

# Thread count for parallel operations
threads=0  # 0 = auto-detect

# Enable verbose output
verbose=false

# Deterministic mode (requires seed)
deterministic=false
seed=

# Security options
mlock=true
secure_zero=true
.fi
.RE

.SH ENVIRONMENT

.TP
\fBGOLDENRNG_CONFIG\fR
Path to configuration file
.TP
\fBGOLDENRNG_SEED\fR
Default seed for deterministic mode
.TP
\fBGOLDENRNG_THREADS\fR
Default thread count override

.SH EXIT STATUS

.PP
.TP
\fB0\fR
Success - operation completed normally
.TP
\fB1\fR
General error - invalid arguments or internal failure
.TP
\fB2\fR
Configuration error - invalid config file
.TP
\fB3\fR
Entropy error - insufficient entropy available
.TP
\fB4\fR
Test failure - statistical tests did not pass
.TP
\fB5\fR
Memory error - allocation or locking failed

.SH FILES

.TP
.I /etc/goldenrng/
System configuration directory
.TP
.I /etc/goldenrng/goldenrng.conf
Default configuration file
.TP
.I /usr/local/bin/goldenrng
Main executable

